I need to identify the profit that an entity retains after all expenses have been deducted, which is typically the Net Profit. Then I need to decompose this into 5 component sub-items from the income statement.

Looking at the income statement:

1. Net Profit is 1095371.35, which is the final profit after deducting all expenses.

2. The 5 component sub-items that are part of calculating this Net Profit are:
   - Total Revenue: 5565589.48
   - Total Cost: 3020000.00
   - Total Expenses: 1180531.44
   - Interest Income: 8592.81
   - Tax Expense: 278279.50

The formula roughly works out:
Total Revenue (5565589.48) - Total Cost (3020000.00) - Total Expenses (1180531.44) + Interest Income (8592.81) - Tax Expense (278279.50) = Net Profit (1095371.35)
